author: Danny Schwartz
title: A. Ros - Killa
text:
0 NOT FEELING IT 0 MAKE IT STOP PREMIERE: Providence, RI singer A. Ros sounds like a latter-day Chris Brown on his new single "Killa." 
The Ocean State is a well-spring of untapped R&B talent. Providence singer A. Ros (pronounced "A Rose") sounds like a latter-day Chris Brown on his sleek new single "Killa." He opens the track by interpolating the B on Marche jingle before launching into an invitation for a certain girl to come and join him in bed. 
"My new single 'Killa ' is about a female that has a man who ain't treating her right," A. Ros told HNHH by email. "That's when I come into her life and show her how she should be treated." 
"Killa" is the second release from A.Rose's next mixtape, which will arrive in April.
